The paper proposes a neural network model for joint extraction of named entities and relations between them, without any hand-crafted features. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, relation extraction. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The model also involves deep learning techniques such as BiLSTM-CRF and biaffine attention, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques such as gradient descent, which is commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a benchmark dataset, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
